summary: Dipterocarpus alatus (Thai: ยางนา, RTGS: yang na, pronounced [jāːŋ nāː]; Khmer: chhë tiël ba:y, chhë tiël tük, chhë tiël thom or ឈើទាល (chheutéal); Vietnamese: dầu nước, dầu rái), also known colloquially as the resin tree, is a tropical forest tree, of dense evergreen or mixed dense forests, in tropical Asia. It is considered vulnerable.
